Analysis.name: Failure to induce clinical remission (subgroup analyses anti-TNF pre-treated vs anti-TNF naive participants)
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: Centrally performed randomization and treatment allocation. Baseline characteristics do not suggest a problem with randomization.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: Low risk
Participants and study personnel blinded to intervention. Appropriate analysis used (ITT).
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Data for this outcome available for all randomized participants.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Protocol prospectively registered. Results consistent with pre-defined parameters.
Overall.bias.support: Due to low risk of bias in all domains.

Analysis.name: Failure to induce endoscopic response
Footnotes: Ustekinumab doses pooled. Only patients with baseline SES-CD ≥ 3 and/or ≥ 1 large ulcer included.
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: Centrally performed randomization and treatment allocation. Baseline characteristics do not suggest a problem with randomization.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: Low risk
Participants and study personnel blinded to intervention. Appropriate analysis used (ITT).
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Not all originally randomized participants took part in this endoscopic substudy as endoscopic data were not an inclusion prerequesite of original study. This seems in accordance with clinical practice and outcome data for all substudy enrolled participants were available.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Protocol prospectively registered. Results consistent with pre-defined parameters.
Overall.bias.support: Due to low risk of bias in all domains.

Subgroup: Ustekinumab (6 mg/kg IV at week 0, 90 mc sc at week 8) versus adalimumab (160 mg sc at week 0, 80 mg sc at week 2, 40 mg sc every 2 weeks)
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: Computer-based randomization. Concealed allocation by independent vendor. No baseline differences that would suggest a problem with randomization.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: Low risk

Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Data for this outcome available for all randomized participants.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Outcome assessors were not aware of the intervention received.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Protocol prospectively registered. Results consistent with protocol.
Overall.bias.support: Due to low risk of bias in all domains.
